Blizzard did not start it, EQ neither.<br>
ALL of these roleplaying games go back to MUDS!!!<br>
<br>
Multi User Dungeon Systems, or something like that.<br>
These games were around, before internet explorer existed.<br>
Some of these games had like 100 to 400 players online, around 1992 or even earlier.(In fact, before internet, there were small ad&amp;d games on BBS's)<br>
<br>
These games only required a telnet application, and you could run them without any problem on a 8086pc (i did play on those then, later on 286 and so on)<br>
<br>
Then slowly new pc's were developed and suddenly there was a pc game market(before atari and amiga were ruling).<br>
Then stand-alone rpg games were created for those pc's.<br>
Wolvenstein 3D was created for amiga/atari. Then Doom was created for the PC.<br>
<br>
During that time, some of the people running muds, started to think about expanding their mud games with graphics.<br>
One of these people, started some group together and they started with Everquest.  They combined the graphics  and the &quot;text based mmorpg&quot; into everquest.<br>
<br>
Diablo was outstanding game, but it was not precessor of everquest. <br>
<br>
PS: nowadays loads of people still play those old text-based games. Facts: They are still cool, they require just a very old pc, that can run telnet, they are social too, they are as addicting as everquest and they are mostly faster. They can be played with a crappy link even and mostly they are totally free.Only thing you miss, are graphics. You only will see text based info.<br>
<br>
